*SED COMMAND -> IT is USED TO REPLACE A STRING IN A FILE WITHOUT OPENING IT AND OUTPT IS DISPLAYED IN THE CONSOLE.
* sed 's/black/red/g' newfile
*sed 's/patter1/pattern2/g'
g->globally
s-> substitute
* sed -i '1 s/hi/bye/ newfile' to save it in same file 

* sed '3,7 s/hi/hello/ newfile' newfile(from 3,7 how many lines are there in 3,7 that we should do the change) 
*sed -n '7,$p' newfile(printing the worksd from first to last>)
SED IS ALOSO USED TO PRINT THE SPECIFIC LINE
