AWK (COMMND)
* it is used to cut the column of a file colum wise and print.
* awk '{print $1}' newfile(THIS PRINT THE FIRST COLUMN) 
* dollar should come front.
*  awk '{print $NF}' newfile (this prints the last file).
number of fields in the current line.(gives the number of files in the current line).
*  awk '{print $(NF-1)}' newfile(TO PRINT THE LAST LINE).
